#TYPES OF FONT SIZES
1.1px->1/96 inch
2.1pt->1/72 inch
3.1em->100% of parent
4.1rem->100% of root

sample code
<style>
    #pixel {
      font-size: 20px;
    }

    #point {
      font-size: 20pt;
    }

    #em {
      font-size: 1em;
    }

    #rem {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    footer {
      font-size: 12pt;
    }

    html {
      font-size: xx-large;
    }
  </style>

#TYPES OF FONT WEIGHTS
1.bold
2.normal
3.lighter/bolder->creates a difference of 100
4.number from 100-900

#TYPES OF FONT FAMILIES
-->comma means the backup option

 #helvetica {
      font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;
    }

    #arial {
      font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    }

    #serif {
      font-family: serif;
    }

    #sans-serif {
      font-family: sans-serif;
    }

    #cursive {
      font-family: cursive;
    }

    #monospace {
      font-family: monospace;
    }

    #fantasy {
      font-family: fantasy;
    }

#TYPES OF TEXT ALLIGNMENT
->there are many types such as left,right,center etc
sample code
#e{
    text-align: right;
   }
